  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/2783",
  "title": "Best practice to format an attribute (price) on the fly",
  "body": "I have a `price` attribute in my algolia index, that is formatted in pences (cents).\r\nWhen I retrieve it, I want it to be formatted in pounds, that is to say divided by 100.\r\n\r\nUsing **Laravel**, **instantsearch 2.6** and **geoSearch widget**\r\n\r\n```\r\nvar map = instantsearch.widgets.geoSearch({\r\n  container: '#map',\r\n  googleReference: window.google,\r\n  customHTMLMarker: {\r\n    template: '<div>@{{price}}</div>',\r\n  }\r\n});\r\n```\r\n\r\n<em>The `@` is because I am using Laravel</em>\r\n\r\nI know those possible options:\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Create a new column in the database `price_formatted`</li>\r\n<li>Use `instantsearch.widgets.hits` to `transformData` - but I don't want to add a widget just for that</li>\r\n<li>Use a handlebar helper - but I have really few clue on how to implement that despite my research</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\nWhat would be the best practice / least resource-consuming to display my price in pounds?",
